@startuml
' @id(STM-CYCLE-LIFECYCLE)
' @ref(DOM-CYCLE)
'
' Objective-side lifecycle of a tracked MDD cycle. Non-trivial: four
' reachable states with externally triggered transitions (skill entry,
' user clarification, /mdd-review parity, user abort).
'
' @desc(STM-CYCLE-LIFECYCLE, "Lifecycle of one Cycle record: Open on entry, looping through clarification and implement/review, Closed only when /mdd-review parity matches.")
title Cycle lifecycle (objective)

[*] --> Open : USE-RUN-CYCLE picks entry\n(generate if description,\nmap-no-comments if none)

state Open {
  [*] --> Modeling
  Modeling --> Implementing : /mdd-validate clean
  Implementing --> Modeling : /mdd-map refreshes current
}

Open --> AwaitingClarification : ambiguous decision\n(skill must ask, never guess)
AwaitingClarification --> Open : user answers

Open --> Closed : /mdd-review parity matches\n(snapshot after/ + write .diff.puml)
Open --> Aborted : user cancels the run

Closed --> [*]
Aborted --> [*]

note right of Open
  While Open: the cycle owns the active
  snapshot. before/ was captured at entry.
  Each implement->map->validate->review
  mismatch loops back here.
end note

note right of Closed
  Terminal success. .mdd/cycles/<n>/ now holds
  the manifest, before/, after/, and the
  annotated <diagram>.diff.puml artifacts that
  USE-CYCLE-DIFF-VIEW renders.
end note
@enduml
